The present study aims to describe the perceptions of the teachers of a group of public schools in the state of Ceará regarding the implementation of the Common National Curriculum (CNC) in the state of Ceará, Brazil. It is a qualitative study based on a phenomenological approach. The research was developed in the state of Ceará, Brazil, with 19 public school teachers. The study was carried out through a questionnaire and the interview. The results showed that the teachers are not aware of the existence of the CNC, or that it is a common curriculum for the whole country. They are aware of the main topics of the CNC, but they are not aware of its content. They feel the need to train themselves to better understand the CNC. They also believe that the CNC will be a good support for the school curriculum. The main contribution of the study is the perception of the teachers on the implementation of the CNC.
